brief_description of the content in the: The JetBrains Inspectopedia page provides a quick-fix solution to convert Javadoc annotations in TestNG tests to JDK annotations.
generated_rule_explanation from GPT-4: The rule 'convertJavadocToAnnotations' checks each Java file for TestNG test methods. If a test method has a Javadoc annotation, it asserts that the method also has a JDK annotation. If the assertion fails, it generates a message indicating that the Javadoc annotation can be converted to a JDK annotation.
PRE_model_validation: The rule is syntactically correct and uses only the built-in functions. It checks for the existence of Javadoc annotations in TestNG test methods and asserts the presence of JDK annotations.
